## Rules

1. Cover every page **and** every interactive state needed by the test plan scenarios above.
2. Run `dom-inspect locate '<selector>'` for every selector before including it in the report — include the match count and visibility in the Validated Locators table.
3. No TypeScript — this report is read by the POM Builder agent; locators only.
4. Use `dom-inspect snapshot` to find `id` and `data-*` attributes; use `dom-inspect aria` for accessible names.
5. Click into dialogs, dropdowns, and menus to capture their DOM state. Re-snapshot after each action.
6. When finished, write the complete report to `{{ output_path }}` using the Write tool.
7. **CRITICAL — no fallback tools.** If `dom-inspect open` or any dom-inspect command fails, **STOP immediately**. Do NOT attempt workarounds using playwright-cli, CDP debugging ports (`--remote-debugging-port`), MCP browser tools, custom Node.js/Python scripts, or any other approach. Only dom-inspect output is accepted by the pipeline. Report the error and stop — the orchestrator will handle the retry.

